Key Match Events: Ryan Dunn led the Suns with 20 points, hitting 6-for-11 3-pointers
Nikola Jokic finished with 21 points, 14 rebounds and nine assists in 30 minutes
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Suns, which lost 109-91 in Detroit to the Pistons, bounced back with a 118-114 victory without Kevin Durant, Bradley Beal and Devin Booker
Others: Jamal Murray was limited to 19 minutes and tallied two points on 1-for-6 shooting, including 0-3 from deep
Russell Westbrook had a solid debut for the Nuggets, ending the night with nine points and six assists
